cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of multi-model and multi-type fitting, which involves learning deep feature embeddings that are clustering-friendly. This problem is closely related to machine learning and computer vision, which are covered by the cs.LG and cs.CV sub-categories. The paper also involves model selection and parameter tuning, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the use of K-means clustering suggests a connection to neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE).
